h27a | Marin County has tried to navigate some of this murky ethical landscape by actively seeking the perspectives of people who use drugs. Initially, only thirteen percent of the people in the county's focus groups opposed wastewater monitoring, while the rest-forty-four percent-supported it or felt neutral. Not surprisingly, the most pressing concern was the possibility that the data could be used for other means, particularly by law enforcement. Yet if the county's strategy can keep the community's trust, a potentially contentious surveillance method could greatly benefit the people it's meant to help.
